    "Fuzzy boundaries, system evolving and unpredictableTABLE 2 PROPOSED STS DESIGN PRINCIPLES (SOURCE: ORIGINAL CONTRIBUTION BY AUTHORS) learning/evolving.",
    "We argue that these human-centered STS design principles will enable AI technology to empower humans.",
    "The other three design principles listed in Table 2-(1) 'flexibility and adaptation,' (2) 'ethical and responsible design,' and (3) 'transparency and explainability'-address the new challenges of AI technology and the emerging sociotechnical characteristics, as highlighted in Table 1 [23], [24], [45], [96].Thus, we believe that these updated STS design principles should help us design human-centered AI solutions in AI-based sociotechnical systems, achieving the goals of the STS approach by balancing AI advancements with human needs and emerging sociotechnical characteristics brought about by AI.",
    "Although these design principles are to be validated and refined through future work, they may help us enrich existing STS theory with respect to AI.",
    "The next section will elaborate on how these principles are applied in developing our iSTS framework."
